%N A397680 Decimal expansion of Integral_{x=0..1} arctan(x)^2 dx.
%H A397680 Michael I. Shamos, <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20220206102634/https://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.366.9997&amp;rep=rep1&amp;type=pdf">A catalog of the real numbers</a>, 2011. See p. 309.
%H A397680 Anthony Sofo and Amrik Singh Nimbran, <a href="https://doi.org/10.3390/math7090833">Euler sums and integral connections</a>, Mathematics, Vol. 7, No. 9 (2019), Article 833. See p. 24.
%H A397680 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-030-02462-8">(Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer International Publishing, 2019, p. 116, eq. (3.95).
%F A397680 Equals Pi^2/16 + Pi*log(2)/4 - G, where G is Catalan's constant (A006752).
%F A397680 Equals Integral_{x=0..Pi/4} x^2/cos(x)^2 dx (Shamos, 2011).
%F A397680 Equals -2 * Integral_{x=0..1} arctan(x)*log(x)/(1+x)^2 dx (Vălean, 2019).
%F A397680 Equals A173623 - A091475.
%e A397680 0.245281203466766431247724397119278822017602763763198...
%t A397680 RealDigits[Pi^2/16 + Pi*Log[2]/4 - Catalan, 10, 120][[1]]
%t A397680 (* Alternative: *)
%t A397680 RealDigits[Integrate[ArcTan[x]^2, {x, 0, 1}], 10, 120][[1]]
%o A397680 (PARI) Pi^2/16 + Pi*log(2)/4 - Catalan
%Y A397680 Cf. A006752, A091475, A173623, A222068.
%Y A397680 Integral_{x=0..1} arctan(x)^m dx: 196521 (m=1), this constant (m=2), A397681 (m=3), A397682 (m=4).
